<subSubSection id="79884658927997BF639B6B1B902CC9EF" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="15FDF7B26E6E27231B95A0FC3916E965" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0B377797D907785A4936C1283A295BF6" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
Head slightly transverse frontally; lower face with long white setae, but setation not as dense as in 
<taxonomicName id="3B989EB769EF79F1E72B01B9085E6098" genus="V." lsidName="V. maculatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="maculatus">
<emphasis id="CC6564F52B57A942B531FFAD0044D55D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">V. maculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="630675523758D0C2C552D8744C6BBD72" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D propodeum, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F antenna G fore wing, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677675" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">3B</figureCitation>
); antenna with scape reaching dorsal margin of anterior ocellus, relatively longer, 5.71-5.86
<normalizedToken id="F55526D0323933FCD4FD2BAF5DE8288E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad; anellus longer than broad; at most F1 about 2.50
<normalizedToken id="060C870052AFFC77EFC410290B042A9A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
a long as broad, other funiculars shorter (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A78C1C0AAC8748B85A0C2C2C8DB14EC0" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D propodeum, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F antenna G fore wing, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677675" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">3F</figureCitation>
); mesoscutellum 1.28-1.41
<normalizedToken id="6D0FBE7111B2AB894A7D80A3C091F048" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
and propodeum 1.71-1.93
<normalizedToken id="B14134C39DC1FC9D727D6BFFA7348CEF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as long (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E8D37D19F672A56645A4E29D4776E0D4" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D propodeum, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F antenna G fore wing, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677675" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">3D, E</figureCitation>
); propodeum between spiracles with two smooth fovea anteriosubmedially delimited by striae on its each side, otherwise longitudinally striate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8FF474797E62A016F957118405361793" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D propodeum, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F antenna G fore wing, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677675" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">3D</figureCitation>
); fore wing slightly obscured, with stronger infumation ventrad to parastigma and clear brown macula surrounding stigmal vein; stigma elongated, not broadening posteriorly, about 2.78-5.00
<normalizedToken id="2A9E987FB4644BEB8DB0C7DC40400598" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="26729B471D9DF015BD229F411919D9DA" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D propodeum, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F antenna G fore wing, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677675" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">3G</figureCitation>
); OI 1.25-1.34.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="051650C9439215BB10A7AA05004337C2" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="description">
<paragraph id="0C746AF44F441FEFD5AAD61A1E5084BC" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="54F74A8F2844F025DF22B6061E451132" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="D0BFC621A9B02A3F104D6A59F1B3ECAB" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Female.</emphasis>
Body length excluding ovipositor 2.12-2.66 mm [holotype = 2.33 mm]; length of ovipositor 0.78-0.96 mm [0.78 mm] (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2DA3BE5280018EEA8F45AA6418D27EB4" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D propodeum, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F antenna G fore wing, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677675" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">3A</figureCitation>
). Most of vertex, upper face including area lateral to supraclypeal area and clypeus, most of mesoscutal midlobe, axilla, mesoscutellum, and callus posterior to spiracle violet. Metapleuron and anterior 0.66
<normalizedToken id="1F55B61967D0C19C6BEF1476D764D259" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
of propodeum blue violet. Temple, lateral panel of pronotum, pronotal collar, mesoscutal lateral lobe, hind coxa dorsally and metasomal tergites with violet tint. Fore wing slightly obscured with stronger infumation under parastigma and clear brown macula surrounding stigmal vein.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E22D3573B0A6F84AAEEDA23E98CC91F9" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="3463734420B492151C4D75B3C78CA259" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="35A6153416242F788BA7C324DEBFDBDF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Vertex and upper face reticulate; clypeus and lower part of supraclypeal area smooth. Head slightly transverse, 1.12-1.19
<normalizedToken id="189A8CFCC61A5B7ADD47C26428E115E4" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[1.19] as broad as high (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2304EAB8DD64D25799DD346219DE3DE5" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D propodeum, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F antenna G fore wing, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677675" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">3B</figureCitation>
); 1.81-1.96
<normalizedToken id="8B9D2B28809439CE7EB2C169453B5F88" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[1.86] as broad as long; 1.34-1.46
<normalizedToken id="4F5D9F370875CD3F0F167AC935835917" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[1.46] as broad as mesonotum at its widest part in dorsal view. Temple short, converging, 0.23-0.38
<normalizedToken id="FC3BBFC273FCA4CE06A59CB76596B76C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[0.26] as long as eye (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="55C52474734690D0D6FA0702FD67C2D7" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D propodeum, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F antenna G fore wing, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677675" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">3C</figureCitation>
). Eyes separated by 1.02
<normalizedToken id="3E969E7BE598A44B9AE867DC63FA2195" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
their own height; eye 1.31-1.42
<normalizedToken id="59CB3C881CD25CDC9206A316193B87CE" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[1.42] as high as long. Upper face with only two rows of setae along eye and scrobes and few additional setae (2-3) between them. Malar space 0.45-0.50
<normalizedToken id="955A7CE14F001A68481EF4DA32E290C8" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[0.50] as long as breadth of oral fossa and 0.37-0.44
<normalizedToken id="121960C06400FA1311CB24E120735907" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[0.39] as long as eye height. Antenna (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F413AC425183070CF6E978D547A9424F" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D propodeum, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F antenna G fore wing, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677675" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">3F</figureCitation>
) with scape 5.71-5.86
<normalizedToken id="91B55167397A070FB70CB413AB09BD35" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[5.86] and pedicel 1.44-1.85
<normalizedToken id="0ED899D89D78EC6E1A474BD0E281CDC2" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[1.50] as long as broad, the former reaching dorsal margin of anterior ocellus. Combined length of pedicel and flagellum 1.52-1.76
<normalizedToken id="A0C93A2B473F43C13F17C102D53ED72F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[1.75] as long as breadth of head. Anellus longer than broad, its breadth slightly narrower than F1 breadth. Relative length/breadth (ratio) of funiculars as follows: F1 2.06-2.53
<normalizedToken id="095BEDA933C6E9A9CD0CCAAC4A059FD8" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[20/8 (2.50)], F2 2.10-2.38
<normalizedToken id="786A93E471350AACDAA316D37D7D191E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[19/8 (2.38)], F3 2.25-2.44
<normalizedToken id="84592C619341CBEE45141BF5B73DC73E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[19/8 (2.38)], F4 2.10-2.22
<normalizedToken id="133D3B8FC0548CA419B9E06C648B904E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[18/8 (2.25)], F5 2.10-2.2
<normalizedToken id="F4ADBF2B85DDBE5D9E2FF47A492C7805" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[17.5/8.5 (2.06)], F6 1.81-1.82
<normalizedToken id="3861CF48682B3B77547606D540E80B66" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[17/9 (1.89)], F7 1.40-1.57
<normalizedToken id="E21EA88870ACD462F0B0CEE7FEA5E470" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[15/10 (1.50)]. Clava with relative length/breadth (ratio) 1.77-2.00
<normalizedToken id="77962360D38E8588963E83283033BB5E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[26/15 (1.73)]. POL 1.31-1.39
<normalizedToken id="092E8B5823F668E6DA65B545703BF020" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[1.39] as long as OOL, OOL 2.20-2.67
<normalizedToken id="C2EC60A47466FFCDFAB438E979E45419" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[2.36] as long as POD. Each mandible with three teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DDF9736B42536CC5F5B9305BF5C80087" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="E729238E6DED371394EB0C74B9CC8356" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="4A34E60BAADFE859F7BB41A638F2523E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Mesosoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Mesosoma about 2.20
<normalizedToken id="C6E5CD9C2EFEE2486DD0AD712414414E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6635E4F27885517A4C524EAA6B91BC2D" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D propodeum, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F antenna G fore wing, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677675" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">3E</figureCitation>
). Pronotum about 0.80
<normalizedToken id="0EF680D467A63B1675725DD4C477B98A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as mesoscutum. Pronotum with pronotal collar about 2.90
<normalizedToken id="57A72BEBE867B83DA0A06D84BC9F5D23" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as long, with few transverse incomplete striae. Mesoscutellum 1.28-1.31
<normalizedToken id="A27A1E533E62C1AD3D88B4221DF18672" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[1.41] as long as broad, with two rows of four setae submedially. Propodeum 1.71-1.93
<normalizedToken id="B20A529A9C3FD86D92743D32832FBC18" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[1.90] as broad as long (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4411BFC9F125109560541D2B823E9B0B" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D propodeum, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F antenna G fore wing, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677675" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">3D</figureCitation>
). Area between spiracles with two small smooth areas anteriosubmedially delimited by striae on its each side, otherwise longitudinally striate; with few long white setae in proximal half. All legs relatively long and slender. Metacoxa about 2.65
<normalizedToken id="FEB2CC0A7D08FA4855C21C4178D0F9AC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad, with long setation dorsally and ventrally; metafemur about 4.75
<normalizedToken id="06B4519890ADC6FA44DF291A0F7C036F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad; metatibia about 7.83
<normalizedToken id="89046A7FA1C7ED52EAA942FF7E5A1715" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad; metatarsus about 0.7
<normalizedToken id="2E39FFFED24217CA9DB2ED0B0D05D0C9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as metatibia. Fore wing 2.63-2.84
<normalizedToken id="5F462F1AC30C29827F527127D7540901" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[2.63] as long as wide, slightly infumated, with stronger infumation ventrad to parastigma and clear brown macula surrounding stigmal vein (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="14CB6DAB6F748B02B74096DDC6065235" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D propodeum, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F antenna G fore wing, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677675" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">3G</figureCitation>
); basal setal line with only three setae dorsally, mediocubital setal line bare dorsally and with about 8 setae ventrally in distal two thirds; marginal vein 0.85-0.92
<normalizedToken id="8DFDA454F8F01DADCC853A3E5F54C4BE" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[0.86] as long as postmarginal vein and 1.38-1.47
<normalizedToken id="FF8252AD173144CE21ECC1964C170F49" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[1.41] as long as stigmal vein; stigma 2.78-5.00
<normalizedToken id="3D21768756A4EC5A6C8C3E822631B99A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[3.20] as long as broad; stigmal vein posteriorly and stigma transparent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D690ED929976F951398D125403F5F266" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="927CB4CE01145D70DB823E53362F82D3" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="314102FC90D16456AB259D694759EC65" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Metasoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Metasoma about 1.05
<normalizedToken id="AC429C1BF642B6A9210F42C45D1488E9" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as mesosoma. Gaster with very shallow alutaceous sculpture and in holotype female compressed laterally; tip of hypopygium reaching about 0.66-0.72
<normalizedToken id="7266D09B40820A37FBA7916162A65322" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
[0.67] length of gaster. OI 1.25-1.34 [1.27].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B92521F8897645BB8CD43713FF22E953" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="E4051FAAEBA1ADD08E51DECF6112A893" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Female variability.</emphasis>
Some specimens have vertex, upper face, most of mesoscutal midlobe, part of axilla, mesoscutellum in posterior third, metapleuron and anterior 0.66
<normalizedToken id="B65C3C4826F108A1FAD7C8BC34AEE534" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
of propodeum green blue; lower face including clypeus, temple, occiput close to occipital foramen and lower mesepimeron in its posterior half brownish with green, blue or violet tint (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6055BEA3C6929E01206354B7090889E3" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi paratypes females A head and mesosoma, dorsal view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, dorsal view D habitus, lateral view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677676" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">4A-D</figureCitation>
). Marginal, postmarginal and stigmal veins after drying with HMDS tend to be bright yellow to white, and hence stigma not transparent.
</paragraph>
<caption id="EEA1B73B3419305F4A97AC2DADFECEA2" doi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677676" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
<paragraph id="BC4831E00B9CFB15B7458EB05AFE7453" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="ACC44B4E3DC7E8BDED7D721AF4660DD3" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Figure 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="68C5FD0F219D3514CBCB9695199AD49C" authorityName="Boehmova &amp; Jansta" authorityYear="2022" family="Casuarinaceae" genus="Vitreostigmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="kangarooislandi">
<emphasis id="421480E03FE95F934020AF74C5DD23BF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
paratypes females 
<emphasis id="612C12DD94114F40867984C5694D647C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">A</emphasis>
head and mesosoma, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="E7A42D65CB809864AB5F7DCDB30CD93F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">B</emphasis>
head and mesosoma, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="9FC8EABCB82E73BD4D36F0F7C7B2A71B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">C</emphasis>
head, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="0EA5D00B213A22F2C438DC7570D973F0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">D</emphasis>
habitus, lateral view. Scale bars: 200 
<normalizedToken id="8426230563CC6EFA7FC0EC313DFD5476" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="CB5B4F29178BB72DF416686A9E7589E4" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis id="F8970D8E26467E82DACA6855D08025B7" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Male.</emphasis>
Length of body 1.40-2.59 mm. Our two males are quite different in metallic coloration The smaller one (CUPC000163) has vertex, mesoscutal midlobe distally, mesoscutellum, and median part of propodeum with a blue violet tint only; stigmal vein light brown, not translucent (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="907D99E872494318A9341EA4C9F03713" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi paratypes, males A habitus, lateral view (CUPC 000163) B head, dorsal view (CUPC 000163) C fore wing, dorsal view (CUPC 000163) D mesosoma, dorsal view (CUPC 000158) E antenna (CUPC 000158) F habitus, lateral view (CUPC 000158) G head, dorsal view (CUPC 000158) H fore wing, dorsal view (CUPC 000158) I propodeum, dorsal view (CUPC 000158). Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677677" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">5A-C</figureCitation>
). The larger specimen (CUPC000158) is more intense metallic blue green as in most females having dorsal part of pronotal collar, mesoscutal midlobe, mesoscutellum and propodeum between spiracles largely blue green with violet reflection and stigma brown with brown surrounding infumation; antenna dark brown with slight metallic reflection except scape beneath (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="75C4D21E47BB3BDA914296CBBA0C564D" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi paratypes, males A habitus, lateral view (CUPC 000163) B head, dorsal view (CUPC 000163) C fore wing, dorsal view (CUPC 000163) D mesosoma, dorsal view (CUPC 000158) E antenna (CUPC 000158) F habitus, lateral view (CUPC 000158) G head, dorsal view (CUPC 000158) H fore wing, dorsal view (CUPC 000158) I propodeum, dorsal view (CUPC 000158). Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677677" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">5E-J</figureCitation>
). Other measurements similar to females except as follows: eyes separated by 1.14-1.36
<normalizedToken id="1543B02E87AA9A417EBD748F1382899D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
their own height; eye 1.28-1.32
<normalizedToken id="034001C25763AC2373635220339068FE" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as high as long; malar space 0.44-0.48
<normalizedToken id="F6DD9E2A64CB75575B3436329813F912" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as eye height; antenna with scape 3.8
<normalizedToken id="BA14DF20DAF35C3D529E8D309E864D76" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad, hardly reaching ventral margin of anterior ocellus; combined length of pedicel and flagellum 2.40-2.58
<normalizedToken id="2FDEE3860CFEEF84900DCDDB82D1C9EB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as breadth of head; ocelli small, POL 1.50-1.61
<normalizedToken id="987D493974C23604612B25286C728601" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as OOL, OOL 1.68-2.25
<normalizedToken id="B5A3472574BC16207E9F11CAD78F3770" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as POD; fore wing with marginal vein 0.71-0.87
<normalizedToken id="D5CFBF245F20604B82D4357CF5D80E5B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as postmarginal vein and 1.56-2.15
<normalizedToken id="8A978677F9F0217C90AD7D877D565BEE" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as stigmal vein; stigma large and broadly ovoid but not elongated, 1.40-1.60
<normalizedToken id="D1DE72DAF67FE3CB3F1FC7223D90B11B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad; propodeum with irregular reticulate sculpture (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="20E0EACFB2ECEFE65DD34D98CB96E867" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi paratypes, males A habitus, lateral view (CUPC 000163) B head, dorsal view (CUPC 000163) C fore wing, dorsal view (CUPC 000163) D mesosoma, dorsal view (CUPC 000158) E antenna (CUPC 000158) F habitus, lateral view (CUPC 000158) G head, dorsal view (CUPC 000158) H fore wing, dorsal view (CUPC 000158) I propodeum, dorsal view (CUPC 000158). Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677677" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">5I</figureCitation>
); all gastral tergite margins straight, not incised medially. Relative length/breadth of flagellar segments as follows: F1 3.75-4.30
<normalizedToken id="C614B18E98BD6C69AF1B4F97BD9E6067" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
, F2 3.33-3.68
<normalizedToken id="7E038CCC192D57B5494493631815F308" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
, F3 3.06-3.33
<normalizedToken id="A0D10B7A226DAD21015ABAA343EB2ECC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
, F4 2.72-3.11
<normalizedToken id="572AC63129AF2623255A549AFBB2BF80" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
, F5 2.66-2.89
<normalizedToken id="AECDE3C847806C78AEA5EF147ED173D5" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
, F6 2.29-2.50
<normalizedToken id="39DE6F08A4C80556C3D509ED7A9642FB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
, F7 1.77-2.18
<normalizedToken id="AFC01E3E85E0F86D99F4021F8353FD69" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
, clava 2.50-3.69
<normalizedToken id="995E34C77C1B82CC2C42D2F1A7CBA098" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
. Funicular segments of the larger male have three rows of MPS, the smaller specimen has funicular segments only with two rows of MPS.
</paragraph>
